to M. Euerard, as also to M. Fisher, to deale with me in this principall Controuersie; and I haue set downe the state thereof, and added thereunto such proofes for the truth, as the holy Scriptures, and the prime Authors in all ages haue offered vnto me. All which I submit to thy diligent examination, and iudicious censure.
               
               
                  
